# Copy to api/.env.remote and fill in your remote DB details (do not commit real secrets).
#
# --- api/.env (local API + node scripts) ---
# In dotenv, # starts a comment unless the value is quoted. Passwords with # or @ must be quoted:
#   DB_PASSWORD="your-secret-with-#-and-@-chars"
# Unquoted DB_PASSWORD=secret@#here  → parsed as secret@ (truncated at #).
# Or use DATABASE_URL and URL-encode the password (# → %23, @ → %40).
#
# Optional — local Postgres superuser/owner for backup_restore_db.sh step 3 only, when
# DB_USER cannot DROP DATABASE (error: must be owner of database):
# LOCAL_DB_ADMIN_USER=postgres
# LOCAL_DB_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# REMOTE_DB_HOST=
# REMOTE_DB_PORT=5432
# REMOTE_DB_NAME=government_projects
# REMOTE_DB_USER=
# REMOTE_DB_PASSWORD=

# Remote pg_dump: backup_restore_db.sh defaults to excluding other,beta,huduma (typical
# permission issues). To override the list or dump everything as a superuser:
# PGDUMP_EXCLUDE_SCHEMAS=other,beta,huduma
# PGDUMP_NO_DEFAULT_EXCLUDES=1
# PGDUMP_SCHEMAS=public

# Kenya wards API: restrict list/cascades to one county (ILIKE). Default in code is Machakos; set empty to disable.
# WARDS_COUNTY_SCOPE=Machakos
